cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it focuses on exploring the comparability of web measurements across vantage points and identifying potential security and privacy concerns. It could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it involves measuring and analyzing internet traffic from multiple vantage points. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves analyzing third-party content and its behavior across different vantage points. The paper also touches upon infrastructure complexity and network fragility, which could place it under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it discusses the implications of these factors on security and privacy.
